joan kennedy former wife of us sen 
edward m kennedy has been scheduled to stand trial sept 13 on a 
drunken driving charge 
the trial date was set thursday after a telephone conference 
between her attorney patrick butler of hyannis and assistant 
barnstable county district attorney richard piazza 
mrs kennedy 51 has pleaded innocent 
she was arrested and charged with driving under the influence of 
alcohol july 5 in craigville on cape cod after the car she was 
driving hit a fence police said she escaped injury 
mrs kennedy refused to take a breath test after the crash 
piazza said refusal to take the test means an automatic 120day 
suspension of her drivers license 
mrs kennedy was fined 200 and her license suspended for six 
months in 1974 after she pleaded guilty to drunken driving in 
virginia 
mrs kennedy who joined alcoholic anonymous divorced kennedy 
dmass in 1983 
