<TEXT>
a cherokee indian reacted to 
reparations paid to japaneseamericans interned during world war ii 
by suing the federal government for uprooting his ancestors in the 
forced march known as the trail of tears 
ive always said if they pay the japanese they should pay 
us said woodrow w bussey who filed the lawsuit in us 
district court friday on his own behalf 
a day earlier the us house passed legislation to give 20000 
each to surviving japaneseamericans who were forced into 
internment camps following the attack on pearl harbor almost 47 
years ago president reagan has said he will sign the 12 billion 
bill 
bussey 71 of albuquerque said he is a cherokee medicine man 
author artist and inventor he said he has not yet found a lawyer 
to handle the case 
if they pay us what they pay the japanese well be happy 
he said in an interview hell i think id happy if they just 
apologized if theyd admit that we had rights and they just 
didnt treat us right 
the lawsuit says members of the cherokee nation were forcibly 
removed from their lands in eastern states and were herded like 
animals on what is now nationally known as the trail of tears 
in the fall of 1838 federal troops gathered tribal members from 
north and south carolina tennessee and georgia and forced them on 
a 116day march across the country to northeast oklahoma 
bussey said he does not oppose the payment to the 
japaneseamericans but believes indians are entitled to the same 
benefit 
they treated the japanese a whole lot better than my people 
although it was still a brutal thing to do he said they 
trucked them to their new houses built fences and fed them 
my aunt told me that they marched the cherokees across the 
country found the worst place they could and then pointed to a 
shady tree and said indian thats your new home 
bussey said he expects other tribe members and representatives 
of other tribes to join in the lawsuit which seeks damages of more 
than 10000 
wilma mankiller principal chief of the cherokee nation in 
oklahoma said friday she has not seen the lawsuit but confirmed 
that bussey was a tribe member she said she would not comment on 
the lawsuit until she could review it 
</TEXT>
