forum a hispanic veterans organization two days after george bush 
told the same group that michael dukakis was for unilateral 
disarmament bentsen told the group the republican accusations 
missed the mark 
mike dukakis supports a strong national defense im strong on 
defense the democratic party is willing to pay the price to defend 
freedom he said 
but he said we wont ever never wink at corruption in 
the pentagon and we wont ever never allow your hardearned tax 
dollars to be used for kickbacks to consultants 
the 2995 billion defense bill vetoed last week by president 
reagan was supported by the secretary of defense and the joint 
chiefs of staff bentsen said 
when reagan vetoed it and bush hailed the action they said 
no to a strengthened role for the military in stopping drug 
traffic they said no to a 41 percent pay raise for our 
service men and women they said no to the biggest defense budget 
in history he said 
unfortunately they also said yes to poisoning defense 
policy with partisan politics he said decisions on national 
defense are now being based on the latest political poll at the 
white house he said 
bentsen received an enthusiastic welcome from the group but the 
400 or so people who listened filled less than half the auditorium 
