check computer terminals to locate resources needed on the fireline 
in some remote mountainous area 
the logistics center keeps shuffling crews in and out of 
hotspots as fire bosses manage to contain one blaze in washington 
only to have a dry lightning storm or a careless smoker spark new 
ones in idaho or wyoming 
just a few days ago a fire blazed in the boise foothills 
outside the centers windows 
the pavement outside the centers huge warehouse is cluttered 
with boxes and equipment especially at night when trucks and 
cargo planes are loaded to fill requisitions while fire crews use 
the cool dark hours to get some rest 
