percent over the next two years the hospital has offered three 
raises of 6 percent each over the next 31 months 
meanwhile negotiations continued in an attempt to avert a 
strike thursday by 1600 nurses belonging to local 790 against two 
public hospitals san francisco general hospital laguna honda 
hospital and city health centers 
local 790 originally set a strike deadline for last monday but 
twice extended it after city health department director dr david 
werdegar and two deputy mayors entered negotiations wednesday 
the public hospitals have been under a wage freeze and nurses 
did not get an expected raise this year the nurses want a twoyear 
contract with a guaranteed 14 percent raise and limits on the 
number of patients to nurses in critical care sections the 
hospitals want a oneyear contract with a continued wage freeze 
the city has an emergency plan if a strike occurs at general 
which cares for the citys poorest and sickest patients and laguna 
honda which cares for more than 1000 elderly the plan includes 
seeking help from hospitals in surrounding counties volunteers and 
