quite baffled by it 
established in 1985 the weekly mail is oriented primarily 
toward white liberals it is respected for its aggressive reporting 
and the generally high caliber of writing 
the government has warned the newspaper twice in recent months 
that it faced a possible threemonth suspension for violating 
censorship rules 
such suspensions were imposed this year on two other 
antiapartheid newspapers new nation and south they have resumed 
publication 
articles in the current edition of the weekly mail include a 
report of black municipal policemen fatally shooting a black high 
school pupil in soweto and a package of stories about a group of 
143 white men who wednesday announced their intention to refuse to 
perform mandatory military service 
one section of the emergency regulations defines as a 
subversive statement any comment construed as undermining the 
conscription system 
the emergency regulations in effect since 1986 also restrict 
reporting about unrest security force actions and treatment of 
detainees 
under apartheid south africa has a racially segregated society 
in which the 26 million blacks have no vote in national affairs 
the 5 million whites control the economy and maintain separate 
districts schools and health services 
</TEXT>
